The problem of returning json with provenance and confidence score is fixed on UAT. However the data I’m getting from TDF is wrong.

Looks like we have failed here on giving meaningful names to the columns. CC @Prashant Kikani
```CREATE TABLE "Mitsubishi Corporation Consolidated Net Income by Segment for FY2022 Q1-3 and FY2023 Q1-3" (
    [(Billions of Yen)] str,
    [FY2022 Q1-3] float,
    [FY2022 Q1-3.1] float,
    [FY2022 Q1-3.2] float,
    [FY2023 Q1-3] float,
    [FY2023 Q1-3.1] float,
    [FY2023 Q1-3.2] float,
    [Change] float,
    [Change.1] float,
    [Change.2] float,
    [FY2023 Forecast (Released Nov. 2)] float,
    [FY2023 Forecast (Released Nov. 2).1] float
);```

> Looks like we have failed here on giving meaningful names to the columns
You mean a meaningful name to the table?

Because actually, we don't give names to the columns. They come directly from the FR outcome.
For context, we generate the table name ourselves.
I mean the columns. Can we check some way what the Form Recognizer did here? Did it just ignore the second row of the header?
Based on looking at the DB of this particular DB, I think FR is giving the second header row as 1st row of the table.
